# Shell scripts run on Linux servers (deploy/install) and in WSL. They MUST use LF.
# With CRLF, Linux bash fails to parse them:
#   `set: pipefail: invalid option name`, `syntax error near unexpected token $'{\r'`.
# eol=lf forces LF in the working tree even on a Windows checkout, and guarantees LF
# in the committed blob regardless of a contributor's core.autocrlf setting.
*.sh text eol=lf

# Config templates consumed by the shell installers / Ruby are safest as LF too.
*.SAMPLE text eol=lf
